* Introduction

I don't actually fancy a dry Martini. 

My preferable gin to vermouth ratio sits anywhere from 1:1 to 3:2. What can I say? I love that classic turn of the century taste!

Some people love dry Martinis, some love no vermouth at all! Some people prefer vodka instead of Gin (not me). Where do you stand on this 100 year old debate? What is the perfect Martini? (leave comments below, I'm interested.)

The truth is that there is none, there is only preference.

** Who is This Crazy Person and Why is He Talking About Martinis?

Hello world! My name is Jeremy Saenz, and I wrote [[http://github.com/codegangsta/martini][Martini]] to help make web development in Go a convenient, expressive, and DRY (pun intended) process. Martini is only about a month old and has gained quite a following already. As of this writing Martini has *161* watchers, *2316* Stars, and *153* Forks on Github. There is a ton of weekly activity around both the [[http://github.com/codegangsta/martini][martini]] and [[http://github.com/codegangsta/martini-contrib][martini-contrib]] repositories.

If you haven't already be sure to check out the [[http://martini.codegangsta.io/#demo][Video Demo]] for Martini.

Martini makes you feel classy. Seriously! I am concurrently typing this article while slowly sipping a glass of scotch. If that isn't classy then I don't know what is!

